WEBVTT

00:05.715 --> 00:08.132
[thunder rumbling]

00:14.473 --> 00:17.224
[panting]

00:17.226 --> 00:20.728
Finally, a galaxy
without trolls.

00:20.730 --> 00:22.104
Huh?

00:25.776 --> 00:27.192
[both grunting]

00:32.116 --> 00:34.783
Your reign of muscly heroism

00:34.785 --> 00:37.411
Ends here, flexulon.

00:37.413 --> 00:38.787
[screeching]

00:38.789 --> 00:41.206
[shouts]

00:42.543 --> 00:44.626
[groans]

00:44.628 --> 00:46.962
Soar high, my golden friend.

00:46.964 --> 00:50.340
For today, we die another day.

00:50.342 --> 00:52.593
[laughing]

00:52.595 --> 00:55.596
[rock guitar solo plays]

00:56.932 --> 00:59.266
[laughs] next stop,

00:59.268 --> 01:02.811
The dank sticky jungles
of bong-ulon five.

01:02.813 --> 01:05.064
-[tires screeching]
-[laughing]

01:05.066 --> 01:06.774
Dude, you shouldn't have
let him eat

01:06.776 --> 01:08.942
That whole pan of acid brownies.

01:08.944 --> 01:11.403
In my defense,
I-I thought it'd be cool,

01:11.405 --> 01:14.406
And I was right.

01:16.327 --> 01:19.953
So, since otto has disappeared
with our bus

01:19.955 --> 01:21.789
And our brownie pans,

01:21.791 --> 01:24.500
Parents will have to drive
their own children to school.

01:24.502 --> 01:27.878
[overlapping complaints]

01:27.880 --> 01:30.047
Well, fewer of you
would have to drive

01:30.049 --> 01:32.800
If you sat down and arranged
a carpool schedule.

01:32.802 --> 01:34.843
[clamoring]

01:34.845 --> 01:36.053
[parent]
I'll kill you!

01:36.055 --> 01:37.930
Or your children could walk
to school

01:37.932 --> 01:39.973
So none of you
have to do anything.

01:39.975 --> 01:41.850
[overlapping agreements]

01:41.852 --> 01:43.227
Walking it is.

01:43.229 --> 01:45.771
However, we do need
one parent volunteer

01:45.773 --> 01:47.106
To complete our team of

01:47.108 --> 01:48.941
Noble crossing guards.

01:50.152 --> 01:53.237
Just, uh, one engaged parent
is all we need.

01:53.239 --> 01:54.988
[overlapping grumbling]

01:54.990 --> 01:57.032
Hell yeah! You know I'm in.

01:57.034 --> 01:58.534
I've been waiting for this
my whole life.

01:58.536 --> 02:01.120
Homer simpson. Wonderful.

02:01.122 --> 02:02.746
Hmm? What'd he say?

02:02.748 --> 02:05.666
I was watching the trailer for
the<i> revenge of the nerds</i> reboot.

02:05.668 --> 02:07.876
John cena is playing booger.

02:07.878 --> 02:11.421
Homer, you just volunteered.

02:11.423 --> 02:13.507
Dear god.

02:13.509 --> 02:15.300
No. Stop. Yield.

02:15.302 --> 02:18.846
Well, he's got the lingo down.
This guy's a natural.

02:18.848 --> 02:19.930
[bird caws]

02:19.932 --> 02:20.931
Now I got to wake up

02:20.933 --> 02:22.599
At the butt-crack of dawn

02:22.601 --> 02:25.769
To walk loser kids
across some loser street.

02:25.771 --> 02:28.564
[groans]
never have children, lenny.

02:28.566 --> 02:31.066
[laughs] you don't have to
worry about that.

02:31.068 --> 02:33.277
-See, I was born without...
-[alert beeping]

02:33.279 --> 02:36.446
What the...? We've got a code
blue in 7-g. Repeat, code blue.

02:36.448 --> 02:38.866
[alarm blaring]

02:38.868 --> 02:40.367
[groans] anyhoo,

02:40.369 --> 02:43.162
You notice there's an apple
for sale in the vending machine?

02:43.164 --> 02:45.831
[laughs] I mean,
who would buy that?

02:45.833 --> 02:47.541
[alarm continues blaring]

02:47.543 --> 02:50.460
-Double the coolant levels, now.
-I'm on it.

02:50.462 --> 02:52.045
Backup pumps on standby.

02:52.047 --> 02:53.630
Carlson, decrease
the steam valves by 60p.

02:53.632 --> 02:55.799
Leonard, the control rods.

02:55.801 --> 02:58.177
You, glasses,
pray for all our souls.

02:58.179 --> 03:00.762
Now, switch generators
on my count.

03:00.764 --> 03:02.222
Five.

03:02.224 --> 03:03.265
Four.

03:03.267 --> 03:05.601
Three.

03:05.603 --> 03:07.477
Two.

03:07.479 --> 03:09.563
Implement.

03:09.565 --> 03:11.398
[powering down]

03:12.443 --> 03:13.859
[laughter]

03:13.861 --> 03:16.320
-We did it!
-Boolah, boolah.

03:16.322 --> 03:17.487
[clears throat] um, fellas?

03:17.489 --> 03:21.450
I'm the nuclear safety guy,
right?

03:21.452 --> 03:25.287
Shouldn't my console have been
doing all that beepy stuff?

03:25.289 --> 03:28.248
-Yeah, um, uh... [stammers]
-uh, you see...

03:28.250 --> 03:30.709
We kind of made it so that
just my console does that now.

03:30.711 --> 03:34.630
We just figured
we'd lighten your load, buddy,

03:34.632 --> 03:36.548
Since you already do so much.

03:36.550 --> 03:37.633
Like the March madness brackets.

03:37.635 --> 03:40.928
And you're the go-getter
who implemented

03:40.930 --> 03:41.678
Jean-short wednesdays.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.340
Are you guys saying

03:45.342 --> 03:47.684
I've never kept anyone safe?

03:47.686 --> 03:51.396
Oh, sure you have, homer.
Just... By not doing anything.

03:57.863 --> 04:00.030
My console isn't even
plugged in.

04:00.032 --> 04:02.616
I opened it, and it's full
of cleaning supplies

04:02.618 --> 04:05.410
And unsold mr. Burns funkos.

04:05.412 --> 04:08.622
[groans] this whole time
I thought I mattered,

04:08.624 --> 04:10.791
But I don't and I never did.

04:10.793 --> 04:11.875
Well, you matter to me,

04:11.877 --> 04:15.254
Especially since
it's Wednesday night.

04:15.256 --> 04:19.591
Oh. Right. Scheduled sex.

04:19.593 --> 04:21.260
[both moaning]

04:21.262 --> 04:24.429
[homer]
okay, here we go...

04:24.431 --> 04:27.266
Just give me a second here.
[moans] come on, just...

04:27.268 --> 04:30.143
Almost... [grunts] um...

04:30.145 --> 04:31.770
[marge]
uh, sweetie?

04:31.772 --> 04:35.065
It seems like your light saber
doesn't want to go "shwoom."

04:35.067 --> 04:37.859
Did you go "han solo"
earlier tonight?

04:37.861 --> 04:40.862
[groans] I guess
I'm useless everywhere.

04:40.864 --> 04:42.489
I'm just gonna
stay in bed tomorrow

04:42.491 --> 04:45.492
And suck my nightstand
ketchup packets.

04:46.537 --> 04:49.538
Actually, you have to
wake up at 6:00

04:49.540 --> 04:50.289
To be a crossing guard.

04:50.291 --> 04:52.040
D'oh!

04:52.042 --> 04:54.626
What do you guys think
happened to otto?

04:54.628 --> 04:55.752
-Jail.
-Jail.

04:55.754 --> 04:57.796
-Jail.
-Maybe he just got tired

04:57.798 --> 04:59.756
Of always running
from the darkness.

05:01.552 --> 05:02.926
Oh, god, there's dad.

05:02.928 --> 05:05.429
Please don't let him
embarrass us.

05:05.431 --> 05:06.930
Well, well,

05:06.932 --> 05:10.642
Time to help the baby brigade
cross the road.

05:10.644 --> 05:12.185
[laughter]

05:12.187 --> 05:14.229
-[groans]
-oh, no.

05:14.231 --> 05:17.733
I deserve your respect,

05:17.735 --> 05:19.651
You little jerks.

05:21.405 --> 05:22.529
Stupid kids. Without me,

05:22.531 --> 05:25.699
They'd be stuck
on one side of the street

05:25.701 --> 05:27.409
For the rest of their lives.

05:27.411 --> 05:30.120
Haw-haw!
Got your octagonal sign.

05:30.122 --> 05:32.122
Hey, give me that!

05:32.124 --> 05:34.458
I need it to tell cars
what to do. Stop!

05:34.460 --> 05:36.126
No, you stop.

05:36.128 --> 05:38.211
-[laughs]
-d'oh!

05:38.213 --> 05:40.630
-[laughter]
-[grunts]

05:43.135 --> 05:44.968
I'm a streetwalker.

05:45.929 --> 05:49.639
Oh, no. I'm late
for my aa meeting.

05:51.101 --> 05:53.185
Hey there, gorgeous.

05:53.479 --> 05:54.561
Hmm?

05:57.775 --> 05:58.732
[grunts]

06:00.060 --> 06:01.485
[both] whoa.

06:01.487 --> 06:04.154
My whole life just flashed
through my pants.

06:04.156 --> 06:05.739
Way to go, homer!

06:05.741 --> 06:08.492
You just saved this
balding little scamp's life.

06:08.494 --> 06:11.286
-All right, homer.
-You did it, dad!

06:11.288 --> 06:13.497
How about one
for the paper, mr. S.

06:15.000 --> 06:16.625
I saved someone's life.

06:16.627 --> 06:17.459
You hear that, world?

06:17.461 --> 06:20.045
Homer simpson matters!

06:20.047 --> 06:21.922
[overlapping shouting]

06:21.924 --> 06:24.132
Oh, right.
How about one of these?

06:24.134 --> 06:26.551
-Whoo.
-Whee!

06:26.553 --> 06:28.136
[grunting rhythmically]

06:30.933 --> 06:32.599
The last two endangered pandas

06:32.601 --> 06:35.477
On earth died today

06:35.479 --> 06:37.437
In what zoo investigators are
calling a grisly murder-suicide.

06:37.439 --> 06:40.565
<i> Adios, pandas. We'll see you</i>
<i> at the crossroads.</i>

06:40.567 --> 06:43.276
We wrap up tonight's
nightly reading of horrors

06:43.278 --> 06:45.737
With a new optimistic segment
I like to call

06:45.739 --> 06:47.739
<i> "chicken soup for the news."</i>

06:47.741 --> 06:50.200
<i> The small-town crossing guard.</i>

06:50.202 --> 06:51.827
<i> [chuckles]</i>

06:51.829 --> 06:54.871
<i> A job most americans consider</i>
<i>as charming as it is pointless.</i>

06:54.873 --> 06:56.164
<i> Until last week,</i>

06:56.166 --> 06:59.292
<i> When local hero homer simpson</i>
<i> risked his life</i>

06:59.294 --> 07:01.336
<i> To save one pumpkin-headed</i>
<i> little boy.</i>

07:01.338 --> 07:04.172
<i> And now,</i>
<i> simpson has become something</i>

07:04.174 --> 07:05.632
<i> Of a curbside celebrity.</i>

07:05.634 --> 07:09.302
What can springfield do to show
its love and appreciation

07:09.304 --> 07:11.012
For local crossing guards?

07:11.014 --> 07:13.807
I don't know. I guess we could
use some new equipment.

07:13.809 --> 07:15.642
These lawn chairs
aren't very comfy

07:15.644 --> 07:18.562
And these old sashes don't
exactly "lift and support."

07:18.564 --> 07:19.521
But you know what, kent?

07:19.523 --> 07:22.816
Keeping kids safe
is its own reward.

07:22.818 --> 07:25.527
God bless that
saintly doughball.

07:25.529 --> 07:27.946
That's it, I'm giving
springfield's crossing guards

07:27.948 --> 07:29.364
An actual budget.

07:29.366 --> 07:32.284
Not for self-serving
political reasons,

07:32.286 --> 07:33.326
But because I'm a man
of principle

07:33.328 --> 07:35.495
Who wants to do good
in the world.

07:35.497 --> 07:38.331
Joseph, your turn
on the sex chess board.

07:38.333 --> 07:41.126
We can't very well play
without our king.

07:41.128 --> 07:44.629
Though the bishop may try.

07:44.631 --> 07:46.590
♪

07:50.304 --> 07:52.179
Wow, look at all
this orange swag.

07:52.181 --> 07:54.973
And that's just the beginning.

07:54.975 --> 07:57.017
Now you'll be getting
a full-time salary.

07:57.019 --> 07:59.311
Ah, sweet cellophane sally.

07:59.313 --> 08:01.104
First, I get paid
to be the timer

08:01.106 --> 08:03.607
At a chess-themed sex orgy,
and now this.

08:03.609 --> 08:06.359
Homer, as the fella
whose heroism got us here,

08:06.361 --> 08:09.696
I nominate you
as crossing guard captain.

08:12.868 --> 08:15.368
[marge and lisa]
ooh.

08:15.370 --> 08:18.163
Look at my handsome man
in uniform.

08:18.165 --> 08:19.748
I don't know, homer.

08:19.750 --> 08:22.792
The only people that wear badges
are power-hungry chumps

08:22.794 --> 08:25.128
Who want to keep
the little guy down.

08:25.130 --> 08:25.962
Are you talking about
that security guard

08:25.964 --> 08:27.297
At the supermarket?

08:27.299 --> 08:30.425
I wasn't trying to break
the gumball machine.

08:30.427 --> 08:32.719
I was just trying
to shake out a purple.

08:32.721 --> 08:33.762
Well, I'm proud of you, dad.

08:33.764 --> 08:36.014
Volunteering to serve
the community

08:36.016 --> 08:38.016
Is the highest calling there is.

08:38.018 --> 08:39.309
You know what's even better?

08:39.311 --> 08:42.229
Volunteering for money.
We're getting paid now.

08:42.231 --> 08:45.565
I even got a budget
for ten more guards.

08:45.567 --> 08:48.568
And I'm only gonna hire
the best and the brightest.

08:48.570 --> 08:49.986
All right, rookies.

08:49.988 --> 08:52.906
Not all of you are going to
make it through training.

08:52.908 --> 08:55.283
Look to your left,
now look to your right.

08:55.285 --> 08:58.286
That's how you know
if a car is coming.

08:58.288 --> 09:00.288
That concludes your training.

09:00.290 --> 09:03.124
Heya, homer.
I-I can't thank you enough

09:03.126 --> 09:04.125
For saving my ralphy's life.

09:04.127 --> 09:08.046
Of course, chief.
Just doing my job.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.881
If you ever need
a parking ticket thrown out

09:09.883 --> 09:12.759
Or someone else's dna left
somewhere, you just let me know.

09:12.761 --> 09:14.803
[humming]

09:14.805 --> 09:16.429
Yarr, captain.

09:16.431 --> 09:19.766
He didn't seek your permission
to cross the seven stripes.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.226
Crossing guard stu

09:21.228 --> 09:24.062
-Thinks he's undermining you.
-[groans]

09:24.064 --> 09:26.481
-Where's the fire, buddy?
-[exclaims]

09:26.483 --> 09:28.358
Do you know how jay you were
walking there, sir?

09:28.360 --> 09:30.527
I-I-I don't know
what that means.

09:30.529 --> 09:32.279
All right, wise guy,
I'm gonna have to ask you

09:32.281 --> 09:33.446
To step out of the curb.

09:33.448 --> 09:34.447
And keep your feet
where I can see them.

09:34.449 --> 09:37.367
[stammers]
I can't even see them.

09:37.369 --> 09:38.618
Sir, calm down.

09:38.620 --> 09:40.161
Look, I can let you off
with a warning this time,

09:40.163 --> 09:44.082
But just so you know,
I run these streets.

09:44.084 --> 09:46.459
I-- what? No, you don't, I do.

09:46.461 --> 09:49.087
Well, I run all the parts
between the curbs. Got it?

09:49.089 --> 09:50.964
Ooh, these are nice.

09:50.966 --> 09:52.424
I'm gonna hold onto them,

09:52.426 --> 09:54.426
Unless you have
a problem with that?

09:54.428 --> 09:57.178
Yeah, no, no problem at all,
um, uh, "cross-ifer."

09:57.180 --> 09:58.930
Just have-have a nice day.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.599
Stupid crossing guards,

10:00.601 --> 10:03.727
Think they're so tough
with their cool orange vests.

10:04.980 --> 10:06.479
Another curb kept safe

10:06.481 --> 10:08.732
By captain
homer j. Simpson. Boys?

10:08.734 --> 10:11.985
♪

10:16.450 --> 10:19.826
[raucous laughter]

10:19.828 --> 10:23.038
H-here's that pitcher
you asked for, squeaky voice.

10:23.040 --> 10:25.123
That's mr. Teen to you, rookie.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.417
These new guys got no respect.

10:27.419 --> 10:29.127
It ain't like when we started
three weeks ago.

10:29.129 --> 10:32.380
Homer, I've been
trying to reach you.

10:32.382 --> 10:36.217
Whoa, there, skinner. This bar
is crossing guards only now.

10:36.219 --> 10:39.012
I don't even let lenny and carl
in here no more.

10:40.057 --> 10:42.265
Yeah, but did you read
my urgent memo?

10:42.267 --> 10:45.352
Tomorrow is the science fair,
bake sale, and picture day.

10:45.354 --> 10:47.812
Morning drop-off
will be very challenging.

10:47.814 --> 10:50.398
Now, uh, I'm not telling you
how to do your job...

10:50.400 --> 10:52.609
Are you telling me
how to do my job?

10:52.611 --> 10:55.195
No, I specifically said I'm not
telling you how to do your job.

10:55.197 --> 10:58.740
That's enough,
principal what's-ya-face.

10:58.742 --> 11:00.533
No pedestrians allowed.

11:00.535 --> 11:01.242
But, homer,

11:01.370 --> 11:03.036
If we don't get this right,

11:03.038 --> 11:05.705
It could be pandemonium.

11:05.707 --> 11:07.374
[scoffs] pandemonium.

11:07.376 --> 11:09.292
It's pandemonium, folks.
This is arnie pye,

11:09.294 --> 11:13.421
Reporting live high above
an elementary school traffic jam

11:13.423 --> 11:16.257
Turned all-out
scholastic fracas.

11:16.259 --> 11:18.593
Surely this town's
handsomely paid crossing guards

11:18.595 --> 11:21.096
Can bring order to this
Monday morning mayhem.

11:21.098 --> 11:23.223
-[helicopter whirring]
-oh, oh.

11:23.225 --> 11:24.683
-Guys, stop it!
-[glass shatters]

11:24.685 --> 11:26.559
[moaning]

11:27.562 --> 11:28.603
[mice squeaking]

11:28.689 --> 11:31.398
-[overlapping shouting]
-[horns honking]

11:32.401 --> 11:35.151
The punching
is making things worse.

11:35.153 --> 11:37.320
Don't make me blow
my whistle at you.

11:37.322 --> 11:40.115
Captain simpson,
the shaking of my car

11:40.117 --> 11:41.491
Is dangerously close to mixing

11:41.493 --> 11:45.161
The hydrogen peroxide, yeast,
and dish soap within.

11:45.163 --> 11:47.247
-So?
-Those ingredients create

11:47.249 --> 11:49.207
A fascinating yet volatile
substance

11:49.209 --> 11:51.251
Known as... [gasps]

11:51.253 --> 11:54.504
...Elephant toothpaste.

11:55.549 --> 11:57.966
This was the most expensive,
destructive,

11:57.968 --> 12:00.677
And disgusting riot since
the isotopes won the pennant.

12:00.679 --> 12:02.429
Go topes.

12:02.431 --> 12:04.347
Crossing guard captain
homer simpson,

12:04.349 --> 12:05.724
What do you have
to say for yourself?

12:05.726 --> 12:07.726
[overlapping shouting]

12:07.728 --> 12:10.478
Um... Um...

