13:26.640 --> 13:28.223
Maybe I should've asked them
for more, just in case.

13:28.225 --> 13:31.559
And, uh, here's some more,
just in case.

13:36.650 --> 13:38.358
Ooh, these beanbag bazookas

13:38.360 --> 13:40.109
Can shatter
a minivan windshield.

13:40.111 --> 13:43.238
[gasps] and it comes
with a beanbag bandolier.

13:43.240 --> 13:46.115
Look at you
and your huge budget.

13:46.117 --> 13:48.326
My big, strong leader
in the streets

13:48.328 --> 13:52.080
And in the sheets--
the bedsheets.

13:52.082 --> 13:54.207
I like that we kept
our sunglasses on last night.

13:54.209 --> 13:57.126
I couldn't see a thing.

13:57.128 --> 13:59.546
Wow, look at all
this cool stuff.

13:59.548 --> 14:03.132
You are an all-powerful
crossing god.

14:03.134 --> 14:05.385
I thought you said
badges were lame?

14:05.387 --> 14:07.428
Hey, like everyone
who comes into a ton of cash,

14:07.430 --> 14:10.348
I've flip-flopped
to the side of authority.

14:11.309 --> 14:14.602
Oh, you're charging me,
francine?

14:14.604 --> 14:17.021
Even though I keep your kids
safe every morning?

14:17.023 --> 14:18.731
Aiden? Charlotte?

14:18.733 --> 14:20.900
Nearsighted nicholas?

14:20.902 --> 14:22.527
Oh, I'm sorry.
It's on the house.

14:22.529 --> 14:24.654
Thank you
for your service, hero.

14:24.656 --> 14:27.824
[sighs] I don't even have kids,
but this guy scares me.

14:27.826 --> 14:29.576
Um, dad,

14:29.578 --> 14:32.996
I worry that this massive
increase in money and power

14:32.998 --> 14:34.998
Is subtly corrupting you.
[chuckles nervously]

14:35.000 --> 14:37.375
Oh, honey, relax.

14:37.377 --> 14:39.961
There's nothing subtle about it.

14:39.963 --> 14:40.962
["won't get fooled again"
by the who playing]

14:40.964 --> 14:41.588
♪<i> hey!</i> ♪

15:02.235 --> 15:03.985
-[glass shatters]
-move, move, move!

15:03.987 --> 15:06.529
[crowd gasping]

15:06.531 --> 15:08.281
Nice job, squeaks.

15:08.283 --> 15:11.400
Moleman, you got a couple
of sjws-- suspected jaywalkers--

15:11.402 --> 15:14.495
At three o'clock.
Engage with extreme hostility.

15:14.497 --> 15:16.831
[moleman over radio]
<i> copy. Gun safety</i>

15:16.833 --> 15:18.791
<i> And body cam off.</i>

15:18.793 --> 15:20.543
[gunshots]

15:20.545 --> 15:23.338
Mm... Simpson
and his orange shirts

15:23.340 --> 15:25.924
Are harassing citizens
with complete disregard

15:25.926 --> 15:27.216
For their civil rights.

15:27.218 --> 15:29.260
I'm up to my eyeballs
in angry emails

15:29.262 --> 15:31.137
And nine-figure lawsuits.

15:31.139 --> 15:34.057
Well, you could always, uh...

15:34.059 --> 15:36.434
Decrease their budget a bit.

15:36.436 --> 15:38.645
-Defund us?!
-[both yelp]

15:38.647 --> 15:40.480
My department does not have
too much money.

15:40.482 --> 15:43.066
How did you know
what we were talking about?

15:43.068 --> 15:45.860
Uh, surveillance satellite.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.236
[beeping]

15:47.238 --> 15:50.949
Aw, geez, we wanted
one of those.

15:50.951 --> 15:52.075
Uh, captain simpson,

15:52.077 --> 15:54.827
Your crossing guards now take up

15:54.829 --> 15:56.454
The vast majority
of this town's budget.

15:56.456 --> 16:00.750
We have no choice
but to trim your budget by...

16:00.752 --> 16:02.961
1.5 percent.

16:02.963 --> 16:06.297
[stammering] one point...

16:06.299 --> 16:08.299
Sir, you're about to learn

16:08.301 --> 16:10.927
The crossing guards
are uncrossable.

16:10.929 --> 16:13.012
[rat squeaking]

16:14.391 --> 16:18.059
Where's the nice man
who helps us cross?

16:18.061 --> 16:20.269
I heard he lost his funding.

16:20.271 --> 16:21.896
Let's just go by ourselves.

16:21.898 --> 16:24.732
[engine revving]

16:24.734 --> 16:26.359
[both scream]

16:26.361 --> 16:29.904
[homer]<i> welcome to</i>
<i> mayor quimby's springfield,</i>

16:29.906 --> 16:32.115
<i> Population: Two less kids.</i>

16:32.117 --> 16:34.492
<i> Quimby and his fat-cop cronies</i>

16:34.494 --> 16:36.202
<i> Want to flood the streets</i>
<i> with door-dashers,</i>

16:36.204 --> 16:38.162
<i> Rolling stoppers,</i>

16:38.164 --> 16:39.080
<i>And yellow-light speeder-uppers.</i>

16:39.082 --> 16:42.959
<i>Joe quimby. Bad for springfield.</i>

16:42.961 --> 16:44.669
<i> Worse for america.</i>

16:45.755 --> 16:48.172
A smear ad?

16:48.174 --> 16:50.466
It's not even an election year.

16:50.468 --> 16:51.384
Is it?

16:51.511 --> 16:53.219
Homer simpson
can bully this town,

16:53.221 --> 16:56.472
Its citizens,
and their young children,

16:56.474 --> 16:58.057
But he cannot bully me.

16:58.059 --> 17:01.894
Clancy, shut him down.

17:01.896 --> 17:03.938
With pleasure.

17:03.940 --> 17:05.064
[gasps]

17:05.066 --> 17:07.233
My anti-quimby ad
got a million likes

17:07.235 --> 17:09.819
On my "thin orange line"
facebook page.

17:09.821 --> 17:11.863
Look at all these
supportive comments.

17:11.865 --> 17:13.114
"murder quimby,"

17:13.116 --> 17:14.157
"dismember quimby,"

17:14.159 --> 17:17.827
"go back in time
and kill baby quimby."

17:17.829 --> 17:19.245
Ah, the internet,

17:19.247 --> 17:21.330
The marketplace of ideas.

17:21.332 --> 17:25.126
You're endangering the lives
of public officials.

17:25.128 --> 17:28.129
Oh, come on, I'm just slinging
a little mud.

17:28.131 --> 17:29.756
What's the worst
that could happen?

17:29.758 --> 17:31.007
[glass shatters]

17:31.843 --> 17:33.426
[gasps] dear god...

17:36.139 --> 17:39.182
That chair was my best friend
on the force.

17:39.184 --> 17:41.184
Who would dare do this?

17:41.186 --> 17:43.102
[wiggum]
me would dare.

17:43.104 --> 17:46.856
When you mess with the pig,
you get the snout.

17:46.858 --> 17:48.274
[snorts]

17:48.276 --> 17:50.193
This is a chair too far, wiggum.

17:50.195 --> 17:51.277
My crossing guards and your cops

17:51.279 --> 17:54.197
Need to settle this
once and for all,

17:54.199 --> 17:57.283
At the most dangerous place
in town.

17:57.285 --> 17:59.410
What, that brunchausen
by loxy place

17:59.412 --> 18:01.621
That's been poisoning everyone
for attention?

18:01.623 --> 18:05.500
No. The six-way intersection.

18:07.629 --> 18:09.295
Well, well,

18:09.297 --> 18:12.632
I thought cops only showed up
after something bad happens.

18:12.634 --> 18:16.052
[laughter]

18:16.054 --> 18:18.012
We are sick
of you crossing guards

18:18.014 --> 18:20.223
And your unaccountable,
super-macho,

18:20.225 --> 18:23.893
Hyper-sensitive,
crazily militarized malarkey.

18:23.895 --> 18:26.771
That's our thing, damn it.

18:26.773 --> 18:28.856
No, that's our thing.

18:28.858 --> 18:30.233
Who the hell are you?

18:30.235 --> 18:32.443
We're ice.
Keeping this country safe

18:32.445 --> 18:34.862
From cleaning ladies
and college-age dreamers.

18:34.864 --> 18:36.614
We're america's heroes.

18:36.616 --> 18:38.866
You wish, kid-cagers.
It's the tsa.

18:38.868 --> 18:41.327
We keep this country safe,

18:41.329 --> 18:44.831
One confiscated shampoo bottle
at a time.

18:44.833 --> 18:46.165
Think again, shoe sniffers.

18:46.167 --> 18:49.127
The only force
holding society together

18:49.129 --> 18:51.462
Is america's meter maids.

18:51.464 --> 18:53.506
And meter butlers.

18:53.508 --> 18:57.135
No, it's us, overzealous
neighborhood watch guys

18:57.137 --> 18:58.886
In right-to-carry states.

18:58.888 --> 19:00.972
-[yells]
-whoop. Sorry, clem.

19:00.974 --> 19:01.681
[clamoring]

19:01.683 --> 19:04.225
[airhorn blows]

19:04.227 --> 19:06.978
You all think
you keep america safe?

19:06.980 --> 19:08.229
[scoffs] how?

19:08.231 --> 19:11.065
By hassling grandmas
and wrecking quinceañeras?

19:11.067 --> 19:12.817
By grazing my junk
with your wand?

19:12.819 --> 19:15.736
Or arresting bank robbers

19:15.738 --> 19:18.030
Who rob banks?

19:18.032 --> 19:19.282
Unlike all of you,

19:19.284 --> 19:21.951
I've earned the right
to feel godlike.

19:21.953 --> 19:24.120
I've actually saved a life.

19:24.122 --> 19:27.165
[lifeguard] um, we save lives
every day, bruh.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.333
Shut up, lifeguards.
This is a land argument.

19:29.335 --> 19:31.711
But if the rest of you
want to get nuts,

19:31.713 --> 19:33.963
Then come on, let's get nuts.

19:33.965 --> 19:35.339
But mark my words,

19:35.341 --> 19:38.009
Before you cross
the crossing guards,

19:38.011 --> 19:40.970
You'd better look
both way-- [grunts]

19:40.972 --> 19:43.598
Hey, everybody. I'm back. I...

19:43.600 --> 19:44.765
Uh-oh.

19:44.767 --> 19:48.895
[groans weakly]

19:48.897 --> 19:49.896
Am I gonna go to jail now?

19:49.898 --> 19:52.565
I wouldn't dream of it.

19:52.567 --> 19:54.150
[cheering]

19:54.152 --> 19:57.778
Well, I hope you learned
a valuable lesson, dad.

19:57.780 --> 19:59.363
Absolute power...

19:59.365 --> 20:00.948
Is the best kind
of power there is?

20:00.950 --> 20:01.866
Is a warm beanbag bazooka?

20:01.868 --> 20:03.910
Does bad things to society

20:03.912 --> 20:06.162
And does strange things to me.

20:06.164 --> 20:10.249
No. Once you militarized
the crossing guards,

20:10.251 --> 20:13.044
They became an army
in search of an enemy.

20:13.046 --> 20:16.047
And if the only tool
you have is a hammer,

20:16.049 --> 20:19.008
Then everything starts
to look like a nail.

20:19.010 --> 20:20.885
Perhaps, but on
the other hand...

20:20.887 --> 20:22.803
-[burps, laughs]
-ugh.

20:22.805 --> 20:24.180
-Mom!
-Gotcha!

20:24.182 --> 20:26.265
Bart, say "excuse me."

